{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":454,"text":"On June 12, 2014, precisely at 3:33"},{"time":6966,"text":"in a balmy winter afternoon\nin SÃ£o Paulo, Brazil,"},{"time":11106,"text":"a typical South American winter afternoon,"},{"time":14632,"text":"this kid, this young man \nthat you see celebrating here"},{"time":17612,"text":"like he had scored a goal,"},{"time":19131,"text":"Juliano Pinto, 29 years old,\naccomplished a magnificent deed."},{"time":26102,"text":"Despite being paralyzed"},{"time":28182,"text":"and not having any sensation\nfrom mid-chest to the tip of his toes"},{"time":33163,"text":"as the result of a car crash six years ago\nthat killed his brother"},{"time":37693,"text":"and produced a complete spinal cord lesion\nthat left Juliano in a wheelchair,"},{"time":45187,"text":"Juliano rose to the occasion,\nand on this day did something"},{"time":50217,"text":"that pretty much everybody that saw him \nin the six years deemed impossible."},{"time":57062,"text":"Juliano Pinto delivered the opening kick"},{"time":62394,"text":"of the 2014 Brazilian \nWorld Soccer Cup here"},{"time":68410,"text":"just by thinking."},{"time":70820,"text":"He could not move his body,"},{"time":72697,"text":"but he could imagine the movements\nneeded to kick a ball."},{"time":77584,"text":"He was an athlete before the lesion.\nHe's a para-athlete right now."},{"time":80838,"text":"He's going to be in the Paralympic Games,\nI hope, in a couple years."},{"time":84300,"text":"But what the spinal cord lesion \ndid not rob from Juliano"},{"time":88882,"text":"was his ability to dream."},{"time":91883,"text":"And dream he did that afternoon,\nfor a stadium of about 75,000 people"},{"time":97933,"text":"and an audience of close to a billion\nwatching on TV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102424,"text":"And that kick crowned, basically,\n30 years of basic research"},{"time":108725,"text":"studying how the brain,"},{"time":110972,"text":"how this amazing universe\nthat we have between our ears"},{"time":114699,"text":"that is only comparable to universe\nthat we have above our head"},{"time":118795,"text":"because it has about 100 billion elements"},{"time":121561,"text":"talking to each other\nthrough electrical brainstorms,"},{"time":124263,"text":"what Juliano accomplished\ntook 30 years to imagine in laboratories"},{"time":129504,"text":"and about 15 years to plan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132107,"text":"When John Chapin and I,\n15 years ago, proposed in a paper"},{"time":136606,"text":"that we would build something\nthat we called a brain-machine interface,"},{"time":141788,"text":"meaning connecting a brain to devices"},{"time":144745,"text":"so that animals and humans\ncould just move these devices,"},{"time":148289,"text":"no matter how far they are\nfrom their own bodies,"},{"time":150140,"text":"just by imagining what they want to do,"},{"time":152726,"text":"our colleagues told us that\nwe actually needed professional help,"},{"time":157313,"text":"of the psychiatry variety."},{"time":160010,"text":"And despite that,\na Scot and a Brazilian persevered,"},{"time":165456,"text":"because that's how we were raised\nin our respective countries,"},{"time":170471,"text":"and for 12, 15 years,"},{"time":172607,"text":"we made demonstration after demonstration\nsuggesting that this was possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176996,"text":"And a brain-machine interface\nis not rocket science,"},{"time":179445,"text":"it's just brain research."},{"time":181171,"text":"It's nothing but using sensors"},{"time":184418,"text":"to read the electrical brainstorms\nthat a brain is producing"},{"time":187965,"text":"to generate the motor commands"},{"time":189971,"text":"that have to be downloaded\nto the spinal cord,"},{"time":192184,"text":"so we projected sensors that can read"},{"time":194847,"text":"hundreds and now thousands\nof these brain cells simultaneously,"},{"time":198362,"text":"and extract from these electrical signals"},{"time":201408,"text":"the motor planning\nthat the brain is generating"},{"time":204293,"text":"to actually make us move into space."},{"time":207256,"text":"And by doing that, we converted\nthese signals into digital commands"},{"time":210942,"text":"that any mechanical, electronic,\nor even a virtual device can understand"},{"time":215934,"text":"so that the subject can imagine\nwhat he, she or it wants to make move,"},{"time":222490,"text":"and the device obeys that brain command."},{"time":225941,"text":"By sensorizing these devices\nwith lots of different types of sensors,"},{"time":229845,"text":"as you are going to see in a moment,"},{"time":231630,"text":"we actually sent messages\nback to the brain to confirm"},{"time":235099,"text":"that that voluntary motor will\nwas being enacted, no matter where --"},{"time":239054,"text":"next to the subject, next door,\nor across the planet."},{"time":244429,"text":"And as this message gave feedback\nback to the brain,"},{"time":247670,"text":"the brain realized its goal:\nto make us move."},{"time":251888,"text":"So this is just one experiment\nthat we published a few years ago,"},{"time":255346,"text":"where a monkey, without moving its body,"},{"time":257673,"text":"learned to control the movements\nof an avatar arm,"},{"time":261777,"text":"a virtual arm that doesn't exist."},{"time":263823,"text":"What you're listening to\nis the sound of the brain of this monkey"},{"time":267025,"text":"as it explores three different\nvisually identical spheres"},{"time":271429,"text":"in virtual space."},{"time":273088,"text":"And to get a reward,\na drop of orange juice that monkeys love,"},{"time":277130,"text":"this animal has to detect,\nselect one of these objects"},{"time":280942,"text":"by touching,"},{"time":282703,"text":"not by seeing it, by touching it,"},{"time":284355,"text":"because every time this virtual hand\ntouches one of the objects,"},{"time":287400,"text":"an electrical pulse goes back\nto the brain of the animal"},{"time":290483,"text":"describing the fine texture\nof the surface of this object,"},{"time":294876,"text":"so the animal can judge what is \nthe correct object that he has to grab,"},{"time":298774,"text":"and if he does that, he gets a reward\nwithout moving a muscle."},{"time":304018,"text":"The perfect Brazilian lunch:"},{"time":306498,"text":"not moving a muscle\nand getting your orange juice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310213,"text":"So as we saw this happening,"},{"time":313017,"text":"we actually came and proposed the idea\nthat we had published 15 years ago."},{"time":317962,"text":"We reenacted this paper."},{"time":319991,"text":"We got it out of the drawers,"},{"time":321960,"text":"and we proposed that perhaps we could get\na human being that is paralyzed"},{"time":325887,"text":"to actually use the brain-machine\ninterface to regain mobility."},{"time":330190,"text":"The idea was that if you suffered --"},{"time":332368,"text":"and that can happen to any one of us."},{"time":334641,"text":"Let me tell you, it's very sudden."},{"time":336653,"text":"It's a millisecond of a collision,"},{"time":338378,"text":"a car accident that\ntransforms your life completely."},{"time":341840,"text":"If you have a complete lesion\nof the spinal cord,"},{"time":344697,"text":"you cannot move because your brainstorms\ncannot reach your muscles."},{"time":348080,"text":"However, your brainstorms\ncontinue to be generated in your head."},{"time":352330,"text":"Paraplegic, quadriplegic patients\ndream about moving every night."},{"time":356245,"text":"They have that inside their head."},{"time":358397,"text":"The problem is how\nto get that code out of it"},{"time":361738,"text":"and make the movement be created again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364662,"text":"So what we proposed was,\nlet's create a new body."},{"time":367883,"text":"Let's create a robotic vest."},{"time":369619,"text":"And that's exactly why Juliano could\nkick that ball just by thinking,"},{"time":374462,"text":"because he was wearing\nthe first brain-controlled robotic vest"},{"time":378781,"text":"that can be used by paraplegic,\nquadriplegic patients to move"},{"time":382060,"text":"and to regain feedback."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383871,"text":"That was the original idea, 15 years ago."},{"time":386768,"text":"What I'm going to show you is how\n156 people from 25 countries"},{"time":392242,"text":"all over the five continents\nof this beautiful Earth,"},{"time":395011,"text":"dropped their lives,\ndropped their patents,"},{"time":398029,"text":"dropped their dogs, wives,\nkids, school, jobs,"},{"time":402139,"text":"and congregated to come to Brazil\nfor 18 months to actually get this done."},{"time":407656,"text":"Because a couple years after Brazil\nwas awarded the World Cup,"},{"time":411531,"text":"we heard that the Brazilian government\nwanted to do something meaningful"},{"time":415183,"text":"in the opening ceremony"},{"time":416881,"text":"in the country that reinvented\nand perfected soccer"},{"time":420621,"text":"until we met the Germans, of course."},{"time":422827,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":424220,"text":"But that's a different talk,"},{"time":426055,"text":"and a different neuroscientist\nneeds to talk about that."},{"time":430095,"text":"But what Brazil wanted to do\nis to showcase"},{"time":432169,"text":"a completely different country,"},{"time":433894,"text":"a country that values science\nand technology,"},{"time":436782,"text":"and can give a gift to millions,\n25 million people around the world"},{"time":440665,"text":"that cannot move any longer\nbecause of a spinal cord injury."},{"time":443500,"text":"Well, we went to the Brazilian government\nand to FIFA and proposed,"},{"time":447104,"text":"well, let's have the kickoff\nof the 2014 World Cup"},{"time":450472,"text":"be given by a Brazilian paraplegic"},{"time":452844,"text":"using a brain-controlled exoskeleton\nthat allows him to kick the ball"},{"time":457734,"text":"and to feel the contact of the ball."},{"time":460010,"text":"They looked at us,\nthought that we were completely nuts,"},{"time":462624,"text":"and said, \"Okay, let's try.\""},{"time":465480,"text":"We had 18 months to do everything\nfrom zero, from scratch."},{"time":469720,"text":"We had no exoskeleton, we had no patients,"},{"time":472956,"text":"we had nothing done."},{"time":474173,"text":"These people came all together"},{"time":476509,"text":"and in 18 months, we got eight patients\nin a routine of training"},{"time":480757,"text":"and basically built from nothing this guy,"},{"time":484855,"text":"that we call Bra-Santos Dumont 1."},{"time":489315,"text":"The first brain-controlled\nexoskeleton to be built"},{"time":492740,"text":"was named after the most famous\nBrazilian scientist ever,"},{"time":496896,"text":"Alberto Santos Dumont,"},{"time":498869,"text":"who, on October 19, 1901,\ncreated and flew himself"},{"time":504672,"text":"the first controlled airship on air\nin Paris for a million people to see."},{"time":511899,"text":"Sorry, my American friends,"},{"time":513918,"text":"I live in North Carolina,"},{"time":515228,"text":"but it was two years\nbefore the Wright Brothers flew"},{"time":520110,"text":"on the coast of North Carolina."},{"time":522274,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":525339,"text":"Flight control is Brazilian.\n(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530117,"text":"So we went together with these guys"},{"time":533117,"text":"and we basically put\nthis exoskeleton together,"},{"time":536018,"text":"15 degrees of freedom,\nhydraulic machine"},{"time":539990,"text":"that can be commanded by brain signals"},{"time":542707,"text":"recorded by a non-invasive technology\ncalled electroencephalography"},{"time":546925,"text":"that can basically allow the patient\nto imagine the movements"},{"time":550114,"text":"and send his commands\nto the controls, the motors,"},{"time":554065,"text":"and get it done."},{"time":555867,"text":"This exoskeleton was covered\nwith an artificial skin"},{"time":558730,"text":"invented by Gordon Cheng,\none of my greatest friends, in Munich,"},{"time":562814,"text":"to allow sensation from the joints moving\nand the foot touching the ground"},{"time":567400,"text":"to be delivered back to the patient\nthrough a vest, a shirt."},{"time":571940,"text":"It is a smart shirt\nwith micro-vibrating elements"},{"time":574910,"text":"that basically delivers the feedback\nand fools the patient's brain"},{"time":579733,"text":"by creating a sensation that it is not\na machine that is carrying him,"},{"time":583204,"text":"but it is he who is walking again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586454,"text":"So we got this going,\nand what you'll see here"},{"time":589313,"text":"is the first time one of our patients,\nBruno, actually walked."},{"time":594003,"text":"And he takes a few seconds\nbecause we are setting everything,"},{"time":596881,"text":"and you are going to see a blue light\ncutting in front of the helmet"},{"time":600178,"text":"because Bruno is going to imagine\nthe movement that needs to be performed,"},{"time":604098,"text":"the computer is going to analyze it,\nBruno is going to certify it,"},{"time":607306,"text":"and when it is certified,"},{"time":609115,"text":"the device starts moving\nunder the command of Bruno's brain."},{"time":612642,"text":"And he just got it right,\nand now he starts walking."},{"time":617217,"text":"After nine years without\nbeing able to move,"},{"time":620003,"text":"he is walking by himself."},{"time":622673,"text":"And more than that --"},{"time":624275,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":627503,"text":"more than just walking,"},{"time":629290,"text":"he is feeling the ground,"},{"time":631608,"text":"and if the speed of the exo goes up,"},{"time":633651,"text":"he tells us that he is walking again\non the sand of Santos,"},{"time":638102,"text":"the beach resort where he used to go\nbefore he had the accident."},{"time":642293,"text":"That's why the brain is creating\na new sensation in Bruno's head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645757,"text":"So he walks, and at the end of the walk --\nI am running out of time already --"},{"time":649456,"text":"he says, \"You know, guys,"},{"time":652180,"text":"I need to borrow this thing from you\nwhen I get married,"},{"time":654811,"text":"because I wanted to walk to the priest"},{"time":657316,"text":"and see my bride and actually\nbe there by myself."},{"time":661090,"text":"Of course, he will have it\nwhenever he wants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664482,"text":"And this is what we wanted to show\nduring the World Cup, and couldn't,"},{"time":668564,"text":"because for some mysterious reason,\nFIFA cut its broadcast in half."},{"time":673618,"text":"What you are going to see very quickly\nis Juliano Pinto in the exo doing the kick"},{"time":681291,"text":"a few minutes before we went to the pitch"},{"time":683588,"text":"and did the real thing\nin front of the entire crowd,"},{"time":686499,"text":"and the lights you are going to see\njust describe the operation."},{"time":689880,"text":"Basically, the blue lights pulsating\nindicate that the exo is ready to go."},{"time":694768,"text":"It can receive thoughts\nand it can deliver feedback,"},{"time":697843,"text":"and when Juliano\nmakes the decision to kick the ball,"},{"time":700861,"text":"you are going to see\ntwo streams of green and yellow light"},{"time":703964,"text":"coming from the helmet\nand going to the legs,"},{"time":706641,"text":"representing the mental commands\nthat were taken by the exo"},{"time":710742,"text":"to actually make that happen."},{"time":712641,"text":"And in basically 13 seconds,"},{"time":715336,"text":"Juliano actually did."},{"time":717419,"text":"You can see the commands."},{"time":719135,"text":"He gets ready, \nthe ball is set, and he kicks."},{"time":723475,"text":"And the most amazing thing is,"},{"time":725353,"text":"10 seconds after he did that,\nand looked at us on the pitch,"},{"time":728585,"text":"he told us, celebrating as you saw,"},{"time":730862,"text":"\"I felt the ball.\""},{"time":733562,"text":"And that's priceless."},{"time":735759,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":737631,"text":"So where is this going to go?"},{"time":739131,"text":"I have two minutes to tell you"},{"time":741066,"text":"that it's going to the limits\nof your imagination."},{"time":744316,"text":"Brain-actuating technology is here."},{"time":746495,"text":"This is the latest: We just\npublished this a year ago,"},{"time":749049,"text":"the first brain-to-brain interface"},{"time":751282,"text":"that allows two animals\nto exchange mental messages"},{"time":754909,"text":"so that one animal that sees something\ncoming from the environment"},{"time":758485,"text":"can send a mental SMS,\na torpedo, a neurophysiological torpedo,"},{"time":764042,"text":"to the second animal,"},{"time":765648,"text":"and the second animal performs\nthe act that he needed to perform"},{"time":769525,"text":"without ever knowing what\nthe environment was sending as a message,"},{"time":773983,"text":"because the message came\nfrom the first animal's brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777279,"text":"So this is the first demo."},{"time":779649,"text":"I'm going to be very quick\nbecause I want to show you the latest."},{"time":783603,"text":"But what you see here\nis the first rat getting informed"},{"time":789192,"text":"by a light that is going to show up\non the left of the cage"},{"time":792125,"text":"that he has to press the left cage\nto basically get a reward."},{"time":795865,"text":"He goes there and does it."},{"time":797658,"text":"And the same time,\nhe is sending a mental message"},{"time":799984,"text":"to the second rat\nthat didn't see any light,"},{"time":803007,"text":"and the second rat,\nin 70 percent of the times"},{"time":805368,"text":"is going to press the left lever\nand get a reward"},{"time":809581,"text":"without ever experiencing\nthe light in the retina."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813716,"text":"Well, we took this\nto a little higher limit"},{"time":817850,"text":"by getting monkeys to collaborate \nmentally in a brain net,"},{"time":822582,"text":"basically to donate their brain activity"},{"time":824772,"text":"and combine them to move\nthe virtual arm that I showed you before,"},{"time":828290,"text":"and what you see here is the first time\nthe two monkeys combine their brains,"},{"time":833058,"text":"synchronize their brains perfectly\nto get this virtual arm to move."},{"time":837316,"text":"One monkey is controlling the x dimension,"},{"time":840116,"text":"the other monkey\nis controlling the y dimension."},{"time":842996,"text":"But it gets a little more interesting\nwhen you get three monkeys in there"},{"time":847176,"text":"and you ask one monkey to control x and y,"},{"time":850983,"text":"the other monkey to control y and z,"},{"time":853654,"text":"and the third one to control x and z,"},{"time":856532,"text":"and you make them all\nplay the game together,"},{"time":858648,"text":"moving the arm in 3D into a target\nto get the famous Brazilian orange juice."},{"time":864602,"text":"And they actually do."},{"time":866987,"text":"The black dot is the average\nof all these brains working"},{"time":871161,"text":"in parallel, in real time."},{"time":874019,"text":"That is the definition\nof a biological computer,"},{"time":877105,"text":"interacting by brain activity\nand achieving a motor goal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881647,"text":"Where is this going?"},{"time":883536,"text":"We have no idea."},{"time":886121,"text":"We're just scientists."},{"time":887921,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":889218,"text":"We are paid to be children,"},{"time":891774,"text":"to basically go to the edge\nand discover what is out there."},{"time":895764,"text":"But one thing I know:"},{"time":897450,"text":"One day, in a few decades,"},{"time":899635,"text":"when our grandchildren\nsurf the Net just by thinking,"},{"time":903157,"text":"or a mother donates her eyesight\nto an autistic kid who cannot see,"},{"time":907475,"text":"or somebody speaks because\nof a brain-to-brain bypass,"},{"time":910403,"text":"some of you will remember\nthat it all started on a winter afternoon"},{"time":916730,"text":"in a Brazilian soccer field\nwith an impossible kick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920502,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922498,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":931962,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947440,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Miguel,\nthank you for sticking to your time."},{"time":951004,"text":"I actually would have given you\na couple more minutes,"},{"time":953529,"text":"because there are a couple of points\nwe want to develop, and, of course,"},{"time":956913,"text":"clearly it seems that we need connected \nbrains to figure out where this is going."},{"time":960810,"text":"So let's connect all this together."},{"time":962712,"text":"So if I'm understanding correctly,"},{"time":964381,"text":"one of the monkeys\nis actually getting a signal"},{"time":966880,"text":"and the other monkey\nis reacting to that signal"},{"time":969146,"text":"just because the first one is receiving it\nand transmitting the neurological impulse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973631,"text":"Miguel Nicolelis: \nNo, it's a little different."},{"time":975855,"text":"No monkey knows of the existence\nof the other two monkeys."},{"time":978746,"text":"They are getting a visual feedback in 2D,"},{"time":981682,"text":"but the task they have\nto accomplish is 3D."},{"time":984355,"text":"They have to move an arm\nin three dimensions."},{"time":986954,"text":"But each monkey is only getting\nthe two dimensions on the video screen"},{"time":990356,"text":"that the monkey controls."},{"time":992132,"text":"And to get that thing done,"},{"time":995150,"text":"you need at least two monkeys\nto synchronize their brains,"},{"time":997964,"text":"but the ideal is three."},{"time":999735,"text":"So what we found out is that\nwhen one monkey starts slacking down,"},{"time":1003351,"text":"the other two monkeys\nenhance their performance"},{"time":1005962,"text":"to get the guy to come back,"},{"time":1007944,"text":"so this adjusts dynamically,"},{"time":1010050,"text":"but the global synchrony remains the same."},{"time":1014399,"text":"Now, if you flip\nwithout telling the monkey"},{"time":1017023,"text":"the dimensions that each brain\nhas to control,"},{"time":1019321,"text":"like this guy is controlling x and y,"},{"time":1021620,"text":"but he should be controlling now y and z,"},{"time":1024035,"text":"instantaneously, that animal's brain\nforgets about the old dimensions"},{"time":1028818,"text":"and it starts concentrating\non the new dimensions."},{"time":1031336,"text":"So what I need to say is\nthat no Turing machine,"},{"time":1034623,"text":"no computer can predict\nwhat a brain net will do."},{"time":1038825,"text":"So we will absorb technology\nas part of us."},{"time":1041206,"text":"Technology will never absorb us."},{"time":1043815,"text":"It's simply impossible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046456,"text":"BG: How many times have you tested this?"},{"time":1049506,"text":"And how many times\nhave you succeeded versus failed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052051,"text":"MN: Oh, tens of times."},{"time":1054327,"text":"With the three monkeys?\nOh, several times."},{"time":1056565,"text":"I wouldn't be able to talk about this here\nunless I had done it a few times."},{"time":1061185,"text":"And I forgot to mention, because of time,"},{"time":1063786,"text":"that just three weeks ago,\na European group"},{"time":1067547,"text":"just demonstrated the first\nman-to-man brain-to-brain connection."},{"time":1072637,"text":"BG: And how does that play?"},{"time":1074157,"text":"MN: There was one bit of information --\nbig ideas start in a humble way --"},{"time":1078739,"text":"but basically the brain activity\nof one subject"},{"time":1085102,"text":"was transmitted to a second object,\nall non-invasive technology."},{"time":1089308,"text":"So the first subject got a message,\nlike our rats, a visual message,"},{"time":1093552,"text":"and transmitted it to the second subject."},{"time":1096106,"text":"The second subject received\na magnetic pulse in the visual cortex,"},{"time":1100588,"text":"or a different pulse,\ntwo different pulses."},{"time":1104094,"text":"In one pulse, the subject saw something."},{"time":1106799,"text":"On the other pulse,\nhe saw something different."},{"time":1108935,"text":"And he was able to verbally indicate"},{"time":1110918,"text":"what was the message\nthe first subject was sending"},{"time":1113958,"text":"through the Internet across continents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116853,"text":"Moderator: Wow.\nOkay, that's where we are going."},{"time":1119372,"text":"That's the next TED Talk\nat the next conference."},{"time":1121689,"text":"Miguel Nicolelis, thank you.\nMN: Thank you, Bruno. Thank you."}]}]}